<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 761.94/106</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-24T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Last paragraph your July 17, 7 p.m. Department assumes that no American
                            rights in Manchuria are impaired, but it awaits more definite
                            information regarding full scope and intent of treaty before giving
                            opinion whether favored nation clause could be invoked if occasion
                            should arise.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>